# Why Does This Work?

Suppose

```text
dp[j]=4
```

That means

There is already an increasing subsequence of length 4 ending at `j`.

If

```text
arr[j] < arr[i]
```

Then we simply append

```text
arr[i]
```

New length becomes

```text
5
```

That's why

```python
dp[i] = dp[j] + 1
```

